Package explicit.graphviz

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Decorator
    A Decorator is called from the DOT output routines and can modify the decoration that is attached at the given node or edge in the GraphViz file.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Decoration
    A Decoration stores the attributes (label and style information) that can be attached to a GraphViz node or edge.
    MarkStateSetDecorator
    A decorator for states: Given a BitSet of state indizes, fills the nodes corresponding to these states with a given color.
    ShowRewardDecorator
    A decorator that attaches rewards to the labels of nodes / edges, according to the given reward structure.
    ShowStateRewardsDecorator
    A decorator that attaches state rewards to the labels of nodes, according to the given reward structure(s).
    ShowStatesDecorator
    Decorator which show the state variable valuation for a given state.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Decoration.LabelType
    An indication of how the node or edge's label should be rendered by Graphviz
